organization.description: The State of Alaska contributes several collections of digital geospatial data and services for government and public use. The Dept of Geological and Geophysical Surveys and the Dept of Natural Resources publish data to data.gov. The University of Alaska also operates the AlaskaMapped and GINA repositories of data.

name: latitudes-and-longitudes-of-volcanoes-in-alaska
notes: This publication provides digital point data for the locations of 127 volcanic centers in Alaska younger than 2 million years. Information about whether a volcano has been historically active is also provided. Detailed information about each center can be found on the Alaska Volcano Observatory website at http://www.avo.alaska.edu
